							<tr>
								<td valign="top" width="100%"><!-- START MAIN CONTENT AREA CONTENTS-->
									<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
										<tr>
											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='header' bgcolor='black' width='100%'>PALADIN STRATEGIES AND PLAYGUIDES</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='spti'>PALLY TIPS, ALL LVL</font> - <small>Zenny Laputa, Brell Serilis</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Here is wut i think a pally can do if anyone reading this
thread feel pally is useless. Any true knight of Norrath should
already know them dou.<br>
<br>
Pally above 50 is not about dmg. Yes, a well equip pally can do
ok dmg, but thats not the point of being one.<br>
<br>
At low lvl 1-25, the point of playing a pally is they can tank
good and solo time to time.<br>
-Yaupl or not to yaup? I would do more testing but since the
melee timer is now changed for spell cast i would say yes 8p<br>
<br>
At mid lvl 26-45, the role of playing a pally become supporting
tank.<br>
-your buff start to be useful, your heal can start to save life
and really help the group on down time.<br>
-Don't forget u get root, a very good tools to help chanter or
anyone being hit in group.<br>
-Puller pulled 5? no problem, hit taunt on 2-3 mobs, park them
away from the fight.<br>
-Cleric or caster getting low but not behing hit atm? give them a
greater heal or two to save mana for cleric and built up the hate
on yourself.<br>
-Puller low on health with 4+ mobs on his back while homing in
camp? don't want for cleric to heal cuz cleric will get blounded,
walk up a little and keep spam the heal to use it as a AE taunt.<br>
-Chanter having trouble mezzing a high lvl or high MR mob? use
your no dmg stun and root. they are chanter's best friend. A war
can walk up to the mob and spam the mob, but if the mob hate the
chanter there is nothing the war can do. But u are different,
using the no dmg stun, u will not break the mez if the chanter
sucessful mez it, u will built more agro then just hitting taunt
so the mob could turn to u easiler, if they both fail, root the
mob to the chanter can walk away and take their time to mez.<br>
-Chanter being hit by 2-3 mobs and cannot get spells off? First
evluate if u need to Lay on the chanter &lt;depends how fast
chanter life going down&gt; if no lay hand needed, first stun a
mob, then walk up root one or root couple, let the chanter know
so he move back and at the same time heal the chanter up a bit
&lt;usually cleric already done it at this time&gt;.<br>
<br>
Lvl 46-54 U start getting couple more stuns, self regen, proc
spell, the class armor of pally &lt;deep water&gt; is relatively
easy to obtain than most classes. It means with a shield u should
have good ac with compairalbe AC with a War with normal gear.
However, u are a better defensive tank then a war, it is because
of your stun spell.<br>
-You are expected to have mastered the above things in mid lvl
range.<br>
-Mobs at high lvl starts to hit very hard compare to player's hp
lvl. Pally is the only tank that can help on this situation for
the following reasons.<br>
-Symbol, make sure all member in your group is symobled, the
higher lvl symbol spells of cleric is very good, but often they
are too expensive to use on all member so cleric might use the
last cheap one &lt;the one with jasper&gt;.<br>
-Root, Parking is very important at high lvl if no chanter is in
group. Because mobs hit so hard, mobs need to be slowed or parked
whenever chanter is not around. Even if slowed mob still do alot
of dmg if u let them keep hitting some of the lower ac class.<br>
-Your stuns, Stuns are the greatest taunt in the game &lt;my
first char is 55 wiz&gt;. First the mobs hit very hard, cleric
cannot keep up without the use of Compelete heal on the big
tanks, if u feel the heal will be late, stun it. It will give u
the extral time needed to compelete the heal. Just before the
shaman slowing the mob, stun it. So the mob will never get a
chance to hit the shaman. Add a stun or two after and the mob
will not hate the shaman anymore. Mob that can Compelete heal or
gate? use your stuns, chain stun it at the end, save your bash at
last resort if all stuns resisted. 50+ mobs in the game don't
reponse to taunt very well, which means spell taunts comes into
effect. SK/Pally at high lvl can out taunt a warrior very easy.
Pally can do it even better because their stun can stop the dmg
output of the mob if the first stun didn't get it off the
caster/healer.<br>
-Deepwater bracer, your deepwater bracer have a stun effect, its
cast time is alittle over 5 sec. Use it in some case will save
your groups life. No chanter in group but the mobs cross
compelete healing each other? use your bracer on the other mob,
the bracer cannot stop melee mob compeltely but it will stop a
caster from casting any spell with cast time longer then 2 sec.
Cleric very lom? use it and chain cast it. It will buy u alot of
time for the cleric to med the very needed CH. Shaman and/or
chanter LD? park it, chain it to buy time while other tank
finishing off the lower ones. U can even make yourself as both
healer/slower on very tank heavy group when chanter/shaman not
aviabalble using helm/bracer combo. In very high lvl raid and NO
ONE can tuant a mob off? stun it&lt;even if it get resisted&gt;
its the best taunt in the game!! I have tried in Seb Jugg raid
for example. Juggs keep hitting on the chanter but no one can
taunt it off, just chain your stuns and it will come to u.<br>
-Plane, playing on plane and get tired of mob running around
between casters?? stun it.<br>
<br>
-If u are a puller, start pulling when the mob start to turn
around &lt;assuming group in good shape hehe&gt;. Cuz pally's dmg
out put is really low, to decrease the down time of the group,
start pulling earlier is better then u spend the time hitting the
current mob in most cases.<br>
<br>
At 55-60<br>
Hum i am a lvl 53 pally myself, so here is just some of the
suggestion i think will work after the big upgrade at
55&lt;spells&gt;. Pally never died! at lvl 55 u get a group heal
with only 2 sec cast time, I would think its a very good taunt if
puller pulled a mess. With the new divine spell plus lay hand and
the disipine at 60, I think it will be very hard to kill a pally
8p. Just make sure others know u are divined. In raid we could be
useful now cuz the divine spell can be useful in some pulls, like
the king in Char, Trak. I am not 57 yet, I hope the Sup heal
works ok on down time. I don't expect it to be very useful at
that lvl dou. but sure we can once become backup healer again.
New symbol would help when cleric is not around. With the lvl60
stacking buff we will be very useful in high lvl adventure.</p></td></tr>
